      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version control with documented test suite; all simulation scripts traceable to a tagged release.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023R2 is used under an FDA-recognized SQA framework. Simulation scripts are version-controlled in a Git repository tagged at v3.0. Automated regression tests cover all boundary condition configurations used in this COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must pass at least one published benchmark problem relevant to rotating turbomachinery flow.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against the Taylor-Couette and lid-driven cavity benchmarks documented in the ASME V&V 20 supplement. Rotating frame implementation verified against analytical solutions for solid-body rotation to machine precision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH quantity of interest must be below 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the nominal pump geometry (coarse: 4.2M cells, medium: 11.7M cells, fine: 31.4M cells). GCI for NIH = 2.8%, satisfying the 5% threshold. Observed order of convergence p = 1.94, consistent with second-order spatial discretization."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match simulated operating points within ±5% for flow rate and ±2% for rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were conducted at 2500 RPM and 3500 RPM across flow rates of 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 L/min. Measured flow rates confirmed within ±2.1% and rotational speed within ±0.8% of nominal values via calibrated instrumentation. Boundary conditions in CFD match experimental inlet/outlet conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH must agree with experimental NIH within 15% mean relative error across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean relative error in NIH across all 10 operating points is 8.3%, well within the 15% acceptance threshold. Maximum point-wise error is 12.7% at the 6 L/min, 3500 RPM condition. Systematic bias is less than 2%, indicating no consistent over- or under-prediction."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH and relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly traceable to the clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the standard FDA-recognized metric for pump hemolysis assessment (ASTM F1841). The relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate directly addresses the COU acceptance criterion of RH < 1. Both QoIs are mechanistically linked to erythrocyte damage through validated power-law hemolysis models."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry family and overlapping operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump, which is the same device family as the COU target. Operating conditions span the full COU envelope (2–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM). Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity matched to 37°C whole blood) was used consistent with COU assumptions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; iterative convergence monitoring sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At Model Risk Level 2, formal numerical solver error quantification beyond iterative convergence is not required. Residuals confirmed below 1e-5 for all equations; mass imbalance below 0.01% across all operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; standard operating procedures and peer review sufficient.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second qualified CFD engineer. Standard operating procedures for boundary condition specification, turbulence model selection, and post-processing are documented and followed. Formal use error analysis not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; model form selection documented with engineering justification.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published literature demonstrating superior performance in rotating turbomachinery hemolysis applications. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) applied consistently. Formal model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must be traceable to measured or published values with documented uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity, density, and power-law hemolysis coefficients are sourced from the experimental dataset (morrison-hemolysis-experimental-dataset, dataVintage 2025-10-22). Geometric inputs are derived from the pump geometry dataset (morrison-pump-geometry-dataset, dataVintage 2025-10-28). The model underwent a minor revision on 2025-11-14 to update the impeller tip clearance from 0.18 mm to 0.21 mm based on revised manufacturing tolerance data; the hemolysis experimental dataset was judged by the assessment team to remain applicable without re-collection, as the fluid property inputs are independent of geometric tolerances. This judgment was made without formal re-validation against the updated geometry, representing an undocumented assumption that the dataset's relevance is unaffected by the model revision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; sample characterization documentation sufficient.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog samples prepared per ASTM F1841 protocol. Lot-to-lot variability in glycerol concentration controlled within ±0.5%. Formal test sample uncertainty propagation not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; qualitative equivalency argument documented.",
      "rationale": "Input parameters used in validation experiments are qualitatively equivalent to those in the COU. Blood analog viscosity (3.5 mPa·s at 37°C) matches clinical CPB perfusate properties. Rotational speed and flow rate ranges span the clinical operating envelope. Formal equivalency quantification not required at MRL 2."
    }
